tary of Kierkegaard's journals based on up-to-date scholarship. It offers new insight into Kierkegaard's inner life. In addition to early drafts of his published works, the journals contain his thoughts on current events and philosophical and theological matters, notes on books he was reading, miscellaneous jottings, and ideas for future literary projects. Kierkegaard wrote his journals in a two-column format, one for his initial entries and the second for the marginal comments he added later. The new edition of the journals reproduces this format and contains photographs of original manuscript pages, as well as extensive scholarly commentary. Translated by leading experts on Kierkegaard, Journals and Notebooks will become the benchmark for all future Kierkegaard scholarship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aPhilosopherszDenmarkvDiaries. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aCappelørn, Niels Jørgen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHannay, Alastair, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKirmmse, Bruce H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPattison, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStewart, Jon, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140087432340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400874323423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400874323.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA